recording: Pressure gauges flutter as a slow tremor runs along the trench walls, metallic echoes rising from depths that feel older than the map
Warm currents shimmer with schooling fish, cameras catching lens flares while a lazy surf of sand rolls across the seabed
Towering fronds sway like cathedral pillars, shadows dart between stalks as stray debris snags and releases with soft thuds
Every ping multiplies into wandering ghosts, guidance systems double check bearings while a distant drip repeats like a metronome
Bioluminescent spires pulse in gentle waves, plankton gather in halos and the seabed glows like a sleeping city
An unknown submarine has appeared here, possible from another expedition? It is carving Cetoan runes into a struce, it says ⚜ ⧫ ⟁ ⦿
Ancient housings vibrate in irregular bursts, loose panels rattle and weak blue arcs briefly stitch the darkness
Water lies glass smooth and reflective, the sub’s lights mirror perfectly while tiny ripples form from no obvious source
A hairline glow leaks from the rift, temperature dips and chains of microbubbles rise in steady columns
Currents whistle through coral corridors, sonar returns loop into melodies and pathfinding loses confidence at every turn
Low frequency pulses throb with clockwork regularity, instruments sync unintentionally and crew report a tingling in their palms
Barnacled beams creak as if remembering cargo, flakes fall like snow and a stubborn mooring light sputters back to life
Kelp twists into slow vortices, beacons drift in lazy spirals and the compass needs constant nudging to hold true
Fields of plankton ignite around the hull like rising constellations, predators linger at the edge of the glow and keep their distance
Loose tools and shells drift unpredictably, thrusters feather to hold position while gravity seems to forget its lines
Clear horizons allow sweeping sonar, distant leviathan calls register as clean arcs and a calm current steadies the mast
Cracked panes shelter small creatures, pearly strings of trapped air escape in bursts and the frame ticks as it settles
A hush rides the ledge with faraway murmurs, thin veils of sediment drift past and the water carries secrets from elsewhere
Light falls off in a single step, sensors widen their eyes and tall silhouettes pass just outside comfortable range
Stone arches frame a broad corridor, pressure wakes ripple across instruments and something immense glides beyond view
Faint alarms echo from the base, hull integrity wavers and distant impacts rattle the structure in an inevitable countdown
